Paper: hep-th/9802069

Date: 1998-02-12

Title: Non-local Field Theories and the Non-commutative Torus

Authors: Micha Berkooz

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B430 (1998) 237-241

We argue that by taking a limit of SYM on a non-commutative torus one canobtain a theory on non-compact space with a finite non-locality scale. We alsosuggest that one can also obtain a similar generalization of the (2,0) fieldtheory in 5+1 dimensions, and that the DLCQ of this theory is known.